<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-224-582  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 224 582.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  March 12 1990 v12 n11 p31(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Vendors offer mirroring solutions. (disk-mirroring for systemfault tolerance)(Sanyo/Icon's Icon 1800, Nonstop Network Ltd'sNonstop Network software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Nonstop Network Ltd and Sanyo/Icon offer disk-mirroring productsthat the vendors claim offer fault tolerant performance equivalentto that expected in Novell Inc's long-delayed System FaultTolerant (SFT) NetWare operating system.andP;  Nonstop offers NonstopNetwork, a $1,290 software utility that runs on any DOSworkstation.andP;  It intercepts DOS reads and writes sent to anylogical drive and duplicates them to any other logical drive onthe network.andP;  Sanyo/Icon's Icon 1800 disk subsystem supports up tosix file servers through its own shared memory adapter andincludes a dedicated system board for disk I/O management andm caching.andP;  Users can plug a second fully configured server into theIcon 1800's port in the event of a server failure.andP;  The Icon 1800sells for $16,160 with 2Mbytes of disk cache memory and one700Mbyte hard disk.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Nonstop Networks Ltd. (product introduction)Sanyo/Icon International Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Nonstop Network (Backup software) (product introduction)Sanyo/Icon International Icon 1800 (Hard disk drive) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Local Area NetworksFault ToleranceDisk DrivesRedundancyFile Servers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>